      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(update): preserve protected Codex routes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Preserve legacy `openai-codex/*` and `codex/*` protected model/runtime routes during non-interactive doctor repair instead of silently rewriting them to `openai/*`.\n- Add update-time protected-route audit/rollback for core update and post-core finalization: if a protected Codex route is rewritten or deleted, restore the pre-update config and fail closed with `protected-route-drift`.\n- Mark cross-provider/auth-route-changing fallbacks in fallback telemetry and keep route-changing fallback notices visible even when upstream verbose fallback output is off.\n- Document the interactive-vs-non-interactive doctor behavior so operators know when routes are migrated versus preserved.\n- Keep interactive `openclaw doctor --fix` migration behavior unchanged.\n\n## Evidence\n\nThis is based on the live incident captured in #80628 and comment https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/80628#issuecomment-4585716866.\n\nObserved on OpenClaw 2026.5.28:\n\n- `openclaw doctor` touched `/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json` at `2026-05-31T04:29:14Z`.\n- A previously working Codex setup had model refs rewritten from a Codex route to OpenAI-provider refs across `agents.defaults.model.primary` and specialist-agent `model.primary` / `fallbacks` entries.\n- The next isolated `News Digest` cron run failed before reply under the Codex harness with:\n\n```text\nRequested agent harness \"codex\" does not support openai/gpt-5.5 (provider is not one of: codex).\n```\n\nLocal remediation was to patch the config back to Codex model refs, remove `openai/gpt-5.5` from the allowed agent model sets, and let the gateway hot-reload. After remediation, `openclaw models status --json` reported `defaultModel` and `resolvedDefault` as `codex/gpt-5.5` with allowed `codex/gpt-5.5` and `xai/grok-4.3`.\n\nThis PR now covers the full failure mode from #80628: doctor preservation, update audit/rollback, missing protected-route deletion detection, and visibility for cross-provider fallback transitions.\n\nRefs #80628, #88450, #88470.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Non-interactive repair and update/finalize flows no longer silently rewrite or delete protected Codex route model/runtime refs.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on this PR branch, Node v22.22.2, pnpm 11.2.2, isolated temporary `OPENCLAW_HOME` and `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH` with no production config or credentials.\n\n### Doctor preservation proof\n\nExact command: created a temporary config containing `agents.defaults.model: \"openai-codex/gpt-5.5\"`, then ran:\n\n```sh\nHOME=\"$tmpdir\" OPENCLAW_HOME=\"$tmpdir\" OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=\"$config\" timeout 90s pnpm openclaw doctor --non-interactive --fix\n```\n\nTerminal capture from the patched branch:\n\n```text\ndoctor exit=0\nconfig after doctor:\n{\n  \"model\": \"openai-codex/gpt-5.5\"\n}\n\npreservation warning lines:\n43:│  - Legacy `openai-codex/*` model refs should be rewritten to            │\n49:│  - Preserved legacy `openai-codex/*` model refs during non-interactive  │\n\nlast output lines:\nUpdated config: $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n  Backup: $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/openclaw.json.bak\nBackup: $OPENCLAW_HOME/.openclaw/openclaw.json.bak\n│\n└  Doctor complete.\n```\n\nObserved result: Doctor completed and wrote the isolated config while leaving the protected model route as `openai-codex/gpt-5.5`; the new preservation warning was emitted in doctor output.\n\n### Update/finalize rollback proof\n\nExact command: created an isolated pre-update config with protected Codex primary, fallback, and model-scoped runtime routes, then created a post-update config where the primary/fallback were rewritten to `openai/*` and the Codex runtime route was deleted. Then ran the real post-core update/finalize path:\n\n```sh\nHOME=\"$tmpdir\" \\\nOPENCLAW_HOME=\"$tmpdir\" \\\nOPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=\"$tmpdir/.openclaw/openclaw.json\" \\\nOPENCLAW_UPDATE_POST_CORE=1 \\\nOPENCLAW_UPDATE_POST_CORE_CHANNEL=stable \\\nOPENCLAW_UPDATE_POST_CORE_SOURCE_CONFIG_PATH=\"$tmpdir/before.json\" \\\nOPENCLAW_UPDATE_POST_CORE_RESULT_PATH=\"$tmpdir/post-core-result.json\" \\\ntimeout 90s pnpm openclaw update --json --no-restart\n```\n\nTerminal/log capture from the patched branch:\n\n```text\nexit=1\nstdout:\n{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"mode\": \"unknown\",\n  \"root\": \"/path/to/openclaw\",\n  \"reason\": \"protected-route-drift\",\n  \"steps\": [],\n  \"durationMs\": 0\n}\n\npost-core-result.json:\n{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"reason\": \"protected-route-drift\",\n  \"changed\": false,\n  \"warnings\": [\n    {\n      \"reason\": \"protected-route-drift\",\n      \"message\": \"Protected model/runtime routes changed during update finalization; restored the pre-update config and stopped the update. agents.defaults.model.fallbacks.0: codex/gpt-5.4 -> openai/gpt-5.4; agents.defaults.model.primary: codex/gpt-5.5 -> openai/gpt-5.5; agents.defaults.models.codex/gpt-5.5.agentRuntime.id: codex -> <missing>\",\n      \"guidance\": [\"Review the config change source, then rerun openclaw update.\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"sync\": {\n    \"changed\": false,\n    \"errors\": [\n      \"agents.defaults.model.fallbacks.0: codex/gpt-5.4 -> openai/gpt-5.4\",\n      \"agents.defaults.model.primary: codex/gpt-5.5 -> openai/gpt-5.5\",\n      \"agents.defaults.models.codex/gpt-5.5.agentRuntime.id: codex -> <missing>\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n\nconfig after finalize:\n{\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaults\": {\n      \"model\": {\n        \"primary\": \"codex/gpt-5.5\",\n        \"fallbacks\": [\"codex/gpt-5.4\"]\n      },\n      \"models\": {\n        \"codex/gpt-5.5\": {\n          \"agentRuntime\": { \"id\": \"codex\" }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"lastTouchedVersion\": \"2026.5.31\",\n    \"lastTouchedAt\": \"<redacted timestamp>\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nObserved result: The update/finalize process exited non-zero with `protected-route-drift`, wrote the post-core result file with both rewritten routes and the deleted runtime route, restored the pre-update Codex config, and did not continue plugin update/finalization.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live production gateway restart on the patched branch was not run; proof uses isolated temp config paths only.\n\n## Tests\n\nLatest validation on head `51390655b51e` after rebasing onto `origin/main` `5b310a7b27f`:\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `pnpm deadcode:dependencies && pnpm deadcode:unused-files && pnpm deadcode:report:ci:ts-unused`\n- `env -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_MARKER -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_KIND node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/cli/update-cli.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.core-send.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.send-validation.test.ts` — 159 tests passed\n- `NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=8192 OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 env -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_MARKER -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_KIND node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/bash-tools.test.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec.path.test.ts src/agents/compaction-planning-worker.test.ts src/agents/code-mode.test.ts` — 130 tests passed\n",
        "branch": "fix-doctor-preserve-codex-routes",
